titleInfo.title: USA v. Robinson
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER regarding PETITION FOR OFFENDER UNDER SUPERVISION 2 as to defendant Jamison Robinson. The defendant should be held to answer for a final dispositional hearing before Judge Bataillon. A final dispositional hearing will be held before Chief Judge Joseph F. Bataillon in Courtroom No.3, Third Floor, Roman L. Hruska U.S. Courthouse, 111 South 18th Plaza, Omaha, Nebraska, on October 23, 2009 at 2:30 p.m. Defendant must be present in person. The defendant is committed to the custody of the Attorney General or his designated representative for confinement in a correctional facility. Ordered by Magistrate Judge F. A. Gossett. (1 Certified copy to USM)(MLF, )

titleInfo.title: USA v. Robinson
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT (For Revocation of Supervised Release) as to defendant Jamison Robinson. Defendant admitted guilt to violation of the mandatory condition which states the defendant shall not unlawfully possess a controlled substance, standard condition #2 and special condition #1 of the term of supervision; Allegations 1,5, and 6 are dismissed on the motion of the United States as to this defendant only. Defendant is committed to the custody of the Bureau of Prisons for 12 months and 1 day with no supervised release to follow. The Special Assessment of $100.00 is paid in full as to defendant Jamison Robinson. Ordered by Chief Judge Joseph F. Bataillon. (1 Certified copy to USM) (KBJ)
